With the improved and advanced technology incorporated by Omron NE-C28 Compressor Nebulizer you can manage and treat your asthma COPD and other respiratory conditions effectively and at your convenience. The Omron compressed nebulizer features Virtual Valve Technology (V.V.T.) allowing you to exhale through your mouthpiece. The valve effectively synchronizes breathing with nebulization hence reducing medication wastage. This virtual valve is safer as compared to the silicon valves used in other conventional nebulizers as it is easy to clean therefore preventing the possibility of infection.

Designed to meet ease of use and comfort needs the nebulizer machine is compact and portable. This compressor nebulizer consists of four main components comprising of the compressor unit air tube medication cup and mouthpiece along with face masks which are used as an alternate interface.

This unit has an easy to operate control buttons and a hose that connects the unit to the mouthpiece and the medication cup. The piston pump built in the compressor unit is designed to ensure prolonged durability and a quiet operation. The air tubes are durable and efficiently carry the compressed air to the medication cup.

The medication cup is capable of holding 7 ml of medication solution. The mouthpiece is comfortable for you to inhale the medication deep into your lungs without wasting the medication.

Performance and Features

Operating with an average nebulization rate of 0.4 ml this device has a high nebulization rate ensuring optimized treatment duration. The gas that flows through the medication solution has a high velocity as the gas flows at a rate of 3.5 l per minute. The particle size is 3 μm hence enabling a quicker delivery as the tiny size of the particle makes it practicable for it to enter your lower airways with ease. The Mass Median Aerodynamic Diameter (MMAD) is 3 μm. The MMAD is the average of the distribution of aerosol mass with respect to aerodynamic diameter.

The NE-C28 compressor nebulizer by Omron operates soundly at a temperature ranging from 10 to 40 deg Celsius and humidity ranging from 30 to 85% RH. The nebulizer machine can be ideally stored at a temperature ranging from 25 to 60 deg Celsius with a humidity ranging from 10 to 95% RH. You can also clean the infrared sensor with a cotton swab therefore meeting hygiene standards.The MC 510 digital thermometer also comes with a beeper guided operation. The device fits comfortably in the ear and beeps to indicate correct positioning and completion of measuring.

The Omron MC 510 model is water resistant with a good memory back up that records the last measurement reading. The temperature indication is in 3 digits in +°C in the unit of 0.1°C. The measuring mode reads in Celsius and Fahrenheit so it gives you the flexibility in switching between the two units. Powered by button cell batteries this Omron ear thermometer allow measurements up to 2000 times. You can use a lithium battery CR2032 with 3VDC. It also includes an auto-off feature which is very important for power conservation. With the thermometers varied services Omron MC 510 is suitable for anyone right from a baby to an adult.

If you are concerned about your blood pressure condition but apprehensive about the constant visits to the clinic then Omron HEM 7201 Upper Arm BP Monitor could be ideal for you. The Omron BP monitor with its ability to provide fully automatic measurement with quick and accurate readings could give you a greater sense of involvement in monitoring and improving your blood pressure condition.

Clinically proven for accuracy the Omron HEM 7201 automatic BP monitor has been tested and validated according to the protocols of Association for Advancement of Medical Instruments European Society of Hypertension and British Hypertension Society. The arm BP monitor features a hypertension indicator apprising you of your hypertension while measuring your blood pressure. The BP monitor also has a movement indicator that detects the movement of the unit thus preventing inaccuracy of readings.

Build

The digital HEM 7201 arm BP monitor offers a very user friendly interface. The control panel consists of a large and easy to read LCD display and one-touch control buttons. This automatic BP monitor comes with a non-integrated medium sized cuff that is easy to attach and fits naturally to the contours of your arm.

With the help the automatic electric pump and pressure release valves the cuff auto inflates to an ideal level thus eliminating discomfort or incorrect readings due to improper cuff inflation. The storage case provided by the BP monitor enhances safety and hygienic standards.

Performance and Features

The Omron HEM 7201 upper arm BP monitor is integrated with IntelleSense technology that enables automatic inflation and deflation thus providing precise readings in just a few seconds. With the personalized inflation and deflation rate there is no pain or discomfort during measurement.

This Omron arm monitor features an advanced averaging mode that allows the monitor to display the average of the last three readings. The BP monitor is also endowed with an automatic memory feature that supports 2 users and is capable of storing 60 sets of readings each along with the date and time of the measurement taken.

The HEM 7201 provides electronic digital readings that shows systolic and diastolic readings as well as pulse rates. The BP monitor displays readings ranging from 0 to 299 mmHg for pressure and 40 to 180 beats/minute for pulse rates. The accuracy rate of the BP monitor stands at +/-3 mmHg for pressure readings and +/-5% of reading for pulse progress. This upper arm blood pressure monitor operates with 4 AA batteries but you also have the option of using electricity as an alternate power source (Adaptor to be bought seperately).
